<TITLE> Bashundhara City closed to public Sat, Sun </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 13 (bdnews24.com)Bashundhara City will remain closed to the public on Saturday and Sunday, said an official on Friday after fire gutted the top eight floors of the building in the heart of the city. The shop owners association general secretary Khalilur Rahman said only shop owners would be allowed to visit their premises during the two days. The country's largest shopping mall houses more than 2000 shops on the first eight floors of the 20-storey building. Rahman said none of the shops were damaged in the fire that engulfed the Basundhara Group's corporate offices on the upper floors. Some merchandise was damaged to due to water poured in to extinguish the fire, he said
